%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221500%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EAmerican%20financier%20Jeffrey%20Epstein%20(left)%20and%20real%20estate%20developer%20Donald%20Trump%20pose%20together%20at%20the%20Mar-a-Lago%20estate%20in%20Palm%20Beach%20in%201997.%3Cp%3EDavidoff%20Studios%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3E%3Ca%20data-autoaffiliated%3D%5C%22false%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdonald-trump%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EDonald%20Trump%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20Friday%20sued%20Rupert%20Murdoch%20and%20two%20Wall%20Street%20Journal%20reporters%20for%20defamation.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThe%20Journal%20reported%20Thursday%20that%20Trump%20wrote%20a%20%26quot%3Bbawdy%26quot%3B%20birthday%20letter%20to%20Jeffrey%20Epstein%20in%202003.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EIf%20the%20suit%20doesn't%20settle%2C%20the%20discovery%20process%20could%20reveal%20new%20details%20about%20Trump's%20ties%20to%20Epstein.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EPresident%20Donald%20Trump's%20latest%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftrump-murdoch-wall-street-journal-lawsuit-docket-mystery-2025-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Edefamation%20suit%2C%3C%2Fa%3E%20filed%20in%20response%20to%20a%20recent%20story%20by%20The%20Wall%20Street%20Journal%2C%20could%20ultimately%20reveal%20more%20details%20about%20the%20president's%20relationship%20with%20the%20late%20financier%2C%20Jeffrey%20Epstein.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETrump%20on%20Friday%20filed%20the%20lawsuit%20against%20Rupert%20Murdoch%2C%20Dow%20Jones%2C%20News%20Corp.%20CEO%20Robert%20Thomson%2C%20and%20Journal%20reporters%20Khadeeja%20Safdar%20and%20Joseph%20Palazzolo.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20suit%2C%20which%20seeks%20at%20least%20%2410%20billion%20in%20damages%2C%20accuses%20the%20group%20of%20committing%20defamation%20by%20publishing%20an%20article%20about%20a%20suggestive%20letter%20bearing%20Trump's%20name%20that%20the%20Journal%20reported%20was%20given%20to%20Epstein%20on%20his%2050th%20birthday%20in%202003.%20Trump%20has%20denied%20that%20he%20wrote%20the%20letter.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EChris%20Mattei%2C%20a%20former%20federal%20prosecutor%20who%20served%20as%20lead%20attorney%20for%20Sandy%20Hook%20families%20in%20their%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Falex-jones-billion-dollar-judgement-2022-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Edefamation%20suit%20against%20Alex%20Jones%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20told%20BI%20that%20the%20lawsuit%20has%20three%20potential%20outcomes%3A%20the%20defendants%20move%20to%20dismiss%20the%20case%20with%20a%20limited%20discovery%20process%2C%20they%20skip%20the%20motion%20for%20dismissal%20and%20move%20instead%20for%20an%20open%20discovery%20process%2C%20or%20they%20settle%20out%20of%20court.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20the%20suit%20doesn't%20settle%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0and%20there's%20no%20indication%20at%20this%20time%20that%20it%20will%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0the%20discovery%20process%20could%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Emake%20new%20revelations%20about%20Trump's%20ties%20to%20Epstein%20public%2C%20Mattei%20told%20BI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20statement%20provided%20to%20Business%20Insider%20after%20the%20lawsuit%20was%20filed%2C%20a%20Dow%20Jones%20spokesperson%20said%2C%20%26quot%3BWe%20have%20full%20confidence%20in%20the%20rigor%20and%20accuracy%20of%20our%20reporting%2C%20and%20will%20vigorously%20defend%20against%20any%20lawsuit.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERepresentatives%20for%20News%20Corp.%2C%20Trump's%20legal%20team%2C%20and%20the%20White%20House%20did%20not%20immediately%20respond%20to%20requests%20for%20comment%20from%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22b2ab149a-c261-4074-89e0-3a994df0bdff%5C%22%3EA%20potentially%20revealing%20discovery%20process%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EDamon%20Dunn%2C%20a%20First%20Amendment%20and%20media%20attorney%2C%20told%20BI%20that%2C%20in%20order%20to%20win%20his%20suit%2C%C2%A0Trump%20would%20have%20to%20prove%20the%20story%20was%20false%2C%20damaging%20to%20his%20reputation%2C%20and%20published%20with%20constitutional%20or%20%26quot%3Bactual%26quot%3B%20malice%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0a%20high%20legal%20standard%20requiring%20the%20plaintiff%20to%20prove%20the%20defendant%20knew%20the%20statement%20was%20false%2C%20or%20acted%20with%20reckless%20disregard%20for%20its%20veracity%2C%20when%20publishing%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20provenance%20of%20the%20'card'%20appears%20suspect%2C%20but%2C%20even%20so%2C%20is%20it%20defamatory%20that%20one%20millionaire%20sent%20a%20birthday%20card%20to%20another%20in%202003%20before%20Epstein%20was%20discovered%3F%26quot%3B%20Dunn%20said%2C%20referring%20to%20the%20time%20before%20Epstein%20had%20been%20convicted%20of%20sex%20crimes.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20discovery%20process%20could%20be%20limited%20to%20whether%20the%20Journal%20published%20with%20actual%20malice%2C%20even%20if%20it%20falsely%20attributed%20the%20card%20to%20Trump%2C%20Dunn%20said.%20That%20would%20be%20similar%20to%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Ewhen%20a%20court%20dismissed%20actor%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fny-times-swipes-news-outlets-after-baldoni-case-dismissed-2025-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EJustin%20Baldoni's%20defamation%20case%3C%2Fa%3E%20against%20The%20New%20York%20Times%2C%20he%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20Mattei%20said%20that%20the%20Journal%20may%20seek%20reciprocal%20discovery%2C%20meaning%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Eit%20can%20ask%20Trump%20to%20provide%20them%20with%20the%20information%20or%20evidence%20he%20has%20not%20only%20about%20the%20writing%20of%20the%20letter%20but%20also%20about%20his%20relationship%20with%20Epstein%2C%20even%20about%20the%20extent%20to%20which%20he%20was%20aware%20of%20Epstein's%20crimes.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20Trump's%20defense%20is%20that%20this%20was%20false%2C%20then%20any%20evidence%20suggesting%20that%20he%20had%20a%20relationship%20with%20Epstein%2C%20the%20degree%20to%20which%20that%20relationship%20was%20close%20or%20not%2C%20would%20be%20relevant%20to%20the%20question%20of%20whether%20or%20not%20it's%20likely%20Trump%20had%20any%20sort%20of%20role%20in%20this%20letter%2C%26quot%3B%20Mattei%20said.%20%26quot%3BAnd%20so%20an%20aggressive%20Wall%20Street%20Journal%20here%20would%20seek%20broad%20discovery%20about%20the%20extent%20of%20Trump's%20relationship%20with%20Epstein.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDunn%20said%20it's%20possible%20the%20defendants%20may%20pursue%20a%20reciprocal%20discovery%20process%2C%20but%20it%20would%20be%20expensive%2C%20and%20Trump's%20relationship%20with%20Epstein%20would%20be%20of%20%26quot%3Bquestionable%20relevance%26quot%3B%20to%20the%20proceedings%2C%20so%20such%20a%20move%20may%20not%20be%20worth%20it%20in%20the%20end.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMattei%20said%20he%20felt%20Trump's%20case%20is%20unlikely%20to%20have%20merit%2C%20describing%20the%20suit%20as%20Trump's%20attempt%20to%20%26quot%3Bexplore%20what%20kind%20of%20power%20and%20leverage%20he%20has%20over%20the%20American%20media.%26quot%3B%20Still%2C%20the%20judge%20will%20decide%20how%20long%20the%20procedural%20elements%20of%20the%20case%20take%20to%20play%20out.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThere%20will%20be%20some%20period%20of%20weeks%20where%20The%20Wall%20Street%20Journal%20will%20be%20able%20to%20file%20its%20motion%20to%20dismiss%20if%20it%20wants%20to%20make%20a%20request%20for%20discovery%2C%20the%20judgment%20rule%20on%20that%20request%20could%20take%20a%20little%20bit%20more%20time%2C%26quot%3B%20Mattei%20said.%20%26quot%3BAnd%20so%20if%20it%20is%20indeed%20contested%2C%20you%20could%20see%20the%20initial%20phase%20of%20this%2C%20including%20discovery%2C%20playing%20out%20over%20the%20next%20six%20months.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2209060243-d585-4a19-8774-0bb51ce47299%5C%22%3ETrump's%20long%20history%20with%20Epstein%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20suit%20against%20Murdoch%20and%20the%20Journal%20reporters%20comes%20as%20Trump%20continues%20to%20grapple%20with%20his%20ties%20to%20Epstein%2C%20a%20convicted%20sex%20offender.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETrump%20has%20said%20that%20he%20was%20friends%20with%20Epstein%20for%20more%20than%2015%20years%2C%20beginning%20in%20the%201980s.%20The%20pair%20were%20regularly%20seen%20socializing%20at%20parties%2C%20and%20Trump%20told%20New%20York%20Magazine%20in%202002%20that%20Epstein%20was%20a%20%26quot%3Bterrific%20guy.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETrump%20said%20in%202019%20that%20he%20and%20Epstein%20had%20a%20%26quot%3Bfalling%20out%26quot%3B%20in%202004%20after%20a%20real%20estate%20dispute%2C%20and%20he%20was%20%26quot%3Bnot%20a%20fan%26quot%3B%20of%20his%20former%20friend%2C%20The%20New%20York%20Times%20reported.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThough%20publicly%20available%20documents%20related%20to%20Epstein's%20sex%20trafficking%20trial%20have%20not%20revealed%20any%20wrongdoing%20by%20Trump%2C%20his%20name%20and%20those%20of%20some%20of%20his%20family%20members%20were%20listed%20in%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fghislaine-maxwell-jeffrey-epstein-little-black-book-contacts-trial-2021-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_self%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Eone%20of%20Epstein's%20contact%20books%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20Trump%20is%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdonald-eric-trump-private-jet-jeffrey-epstein-ghislaine-maxwell-trial-2021-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_self%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Ementioned%20as%20a%20passenger%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftrump-jeffrey-epstein-private-jet-weekend-campaign-2024-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_self%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Eflight%20logs%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20Epstein's%20private%20jets.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20part%20of%20his%20reelection%20campaign%2C%20Trump%20promised%20he%20would%20make%20public%20all%20the%20available%20files%20related%20to%20the%20government's%20investigation%20into%20Epstein's%20crimes.%20After%20taking%20office%2C%20he%20ch