C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F68781ae73d5881a51c1d78de%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221000%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%3Cp%3EGetty%20Images%3B%20Alyssa%20Powell%2FBI%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EBill%20Stewart%2C%20the%20owner%20of%20LI%20Toy%20and%20Game%20on%20Long%20Island%2C%20New%20York%2C%20estimates%20that%20he%20gets%20%26quot%3Bscrewed%20over%26quot%3B%20by%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Freturn-frauds-big-foe-ai-program-that-can-spot-counterfeits-2024-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ereturn%20shenanigans%3C%2Fa%3E%20twice%20a%20month.%20Customers%20falsely%20claim%20an%20item%20he%20shipped%20wasn't%20as%20described%20or%20doesn't%20work%2C%20or%20they%20send%20back%20something%20in%20much%20worse%20condition%20than%20how%20he%20released%20it.%20Recently%2C%20a%20customer%20returned%20a%20Scooby%20Doo%20Mystery%20Machine%20model%20kit%20after%20two%20weeks%20with%20the%20box%20open%2C%20the%20toy%20half%20assembled%2C%20and%20pieces%20missing.%20Given%20the%20condition%2C%20there%20was%20no%20way%20for%20him%20to%20resell%20it.%20%26quot%3BWent%20right%20into%20the%20trash%2C%26quot%3B%20Stewart%20says.%20%26quot%3BThe%20kid%20played%20with%20it%2C%20was%20probably%20too%20young%20for%20it.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAdding%20up%20the%20price%20of%20the%20item%20itself%2C%20two-way%20shipping%20costs%2C%20and%20merchant%20fees%20charged%20by%20the%20third-party%20platform%20he%20used%20to%20sell%20the%20item%20%E2%80%94%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhat-is-walmart-marketplace-for-third-party-sellers2023-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EWalmart%20Marketplace%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20in%20this%20case%20%E2%80%94%20Stewart%20estimates%20the%20exchange%20resulted%20in%20a%20net%20loss%20of%20%2455.%20For%20the%20big%20guys%2C%20he%20recognizes%20that's%20nothing%2C%20but%20for%20a%20small%20business%20like%20his%2C%20it's%20a%20hit%2C%20and%20one%20for%20which%20he%20has%20no%20recourse.%20%26quot%3BWith%20Walmart%2C%20the%20customer's%20always%20right%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20ability%20to%20return%20an%20item%20you've%20purchased%20has%20become%20a%20core%20part%20of%20the%20shopping%20experience.%20Customers%20may%20buy%20a%20few%20more%20items%20than%20they%20would%20otherwise%20because%20it's%20a%20no-harm%2C%20no-foul%20situation%20on%20returns.%20Backsies%20are%20allowed.%20But%20retailers%20say%20consumers%20are%20engaging%20in%20%3Cem%3Etoo%20many%20%3C%2Fem%3Ebacksies.%20Some%20are%20committing%20outright%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fstealing-amazon-whole-foods-jeff-bezos-retail-theft-fraud-2025-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ereturn%20fraud%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%20shipping%20back%20empty%20boxes%2C%20swapping%20out%20different%20items%2C%20or%20claiming%20a%20package%20never%20arrived.%20Others%20are%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fonline-returns-digital-shoplifting-wardrobing-fees-fashion-chargebacks-2025-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eabusing%20generous%20return%20policies%3C%2Fa%3E%20by%20attempting%20to%20send%20back%20items%20after%20days%2C%20weeks%2C%20and%20even%20months%20of%20use.%20And%20while%20it's%20tempting%20to%20blame%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fretailers-lost-millions-in-organized-online-refund-fraud-scheme-2023-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eorganized%20criminals%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20retailers%20and%20return%20logistics%20operators%20say%20a%20lot%20of%20everyday%20consumers%20are%20the%20culprits%2C%20too.%20People%20are%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Flow-buy-year-reduce-consumption-needless-spending-saving-fast-fashion-2025-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Estrapped%20for%20cash%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20they've%20been%20trained%20to%20expect%20super%20loose%20return%20policies%2C%20and%20they%20don't%20feel%20bad%20about%20pulling%20one%20over%20on%20a%20faceless%20company.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BConsumers%20who%20would%20never%20go%20into%20a%20physical%20store%20and%20take%20an%20item%20off%20without%20paying%20and%20stealing%20are%20actually%20being%20trained%20socially%20that%20it's%20actually%20acceptable%20to%20take%20advantage%20of%20retailers%20in%20these%20small%20ways%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20David%20Morin%2C%20the%20vice%20president%20of%20client%20strategy%20at%20Narvar%2C%20a%20retail%20logistics%20company.%20%26quot%3BThey%20think%20it's%20OK%2C%20right%3F%20Stick%20it%20to%20the%20man.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAmerica%20is%20becoming%20a%20nation%20of%20small-time%20return%20fraudsters%2C%20one%20box%20of%20fibs%20at%20a%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EA%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businesswire.com%2Fnews%2Fhome%2F20241230601195%2Fen%2FAppriss-Retail-Annual-Research-Fraudulent-Returns-and-Claims-Cost-Retailers-%2524103B-in-2024%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Erecent%20report%3C%2Fa%3E%20from%20Appriss%20Retail%20and%20Deloitte%20found%20that%20the%20total%20value%20of%20merchandise%20returned%20in%20the%20US%20reached%20%24685%20billion%20in%202024.%20Fifteen%20percent%20of%20that%20%E2%80%94%20%24103%20billion%20%E2%80%94%20was%20fraudulent%2C%20the%20report%20said%2C%20meaning%20the%20product%20shouldn't%20have%20qualified%20for%20a%20refund%20under%20the%20retailer's%20policies.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMorin%20says%20it's%20hard%20to%20suss%20out%20who%2C%20specifically%2C%20is%20responsible%20for%20fraudulent%20behavior%20%E2%80%94%20organized%20criminals%20versus%20everyday%20consumers%20%E2%80%94%20but%20it's%20clear%20that%20a%20wider%20range%20of%20people%20are%20partaking%20than%20you%20may%20expect.%20In%202024%2C%20Narvar%20ran%20a%20survey%20of%20US%20consumers%20that%20found%20that%20more%20than%20half%20of%20consumers%20admitted%20to%20engaging%20in%20fraudulent%20returns%20at%20least%20once.%20In%20a%20separate%202023%20survey%20of%20US%20online%20shoppers%20from%20Loop%20Returns%2C%20a%20returns%20management%20software%20company%2C%20nearly%20four%20in%2010%20people%20admitted%20to%20having%20engaged%20in%20returns%20policy%20abuse%20themselves%20or%20knowing%20of%20someone%20who%20had.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThere%20seems%20to%20be%20this%20mentality%20that%20consumers%20feel%20entitled%20to%20do%20it%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20Jessica%20Meher%2C%20the%20senior%20vice%20president%20of%20marketing%20at%20Loop.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20spectrum%20of%20returns%20mischief%20is%20quite%20broad%2C%20and%20your%20mileage%20may%20vary%20on%20what's%20acceptable%20versus%20what's%20abuse.%20On%20the%20more%20benign%20end%20is%20%26quot%3B%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbracketing-online-shopping-downsides-explained-2021-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ebracketing%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%26quot%3B%20when%20consumers%20buy%20the%20same%20item%20in%20different%20sizes%20or%20colors%20and%20send%20back%20whatever%20doesn't%20work.%20It's%20a%20logistical%20headache%20and%20bad%20for%20the%20environment%2C%20but%20it's%20generally%20above%20board.%20Inching%20into%20the%20fraud%20territory%20is%20the%20practice%20known%20as%20%26quot%3B%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fonline-shopping-return-policies-create-bad-habits-culture-2023-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ewardrobing%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%26quot%3B%20which%20Thomas%20Borders%2C%20the%20vice%20president%20of%20operations%20for%20Inmar%20Supply%20Chain%2C%20a%20reverse%20logistics%20company%20recently%20acquired%20by%20DHL%2C%20says%20is%20when%20consumers%20treat%20return%20windows%20as%20%26quot%3Bfree%20rentals.%26quot%3B%20The%20practice%20will%20sound%20familiar%20to%20a%20lot%20of%20shoppers%3A%20You%20buy%20a%20dress%20or%20a%20pair%20of%20shoes%20for%20a%20special%20occasion%2C%20you%20wear%20it%20to%20said%20special%20occasion%2C%20and%20then%20you%20return%20it%20and%20get%20your%20money%20back.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIn%20an%20effort%20to%20avoid%20customer%20dissatisfaction%2C%20retailers%20will%20process%20the%20consumers'%20refund%20before%20items%20are%20properly%20assessed%20and%20any%20damage%20identified%2C%26quot%3B%20Borders%20says.%20%26quot%3BThis%20results%20in%20premature%20refunds%2C%20leaving%20retailers%20with%20very%20little%20recourse.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EE-commerce%20makes%20this%20sort%20of%20return%20abuse%20even%20easier%20to%20engage%20in%20than%20brick-and-mortar%20shopping%20%E2%80%94%20warehouse%20employees%20often%20don't%20closely%20scrutinize%20every%20single%20item%20to%20make%20sure%20it's%20in%20tip-top%20condition%20like%20employees%20at%20a%20retail%20counter%20might.%20In%20a%20digital%20world%2C%20the%20retailer%20will%20probably%20see%20the%20wine%20stains%20on%20the%20dress%20you%20wore%20to%20that%20wedding%20only%20when%20it's%20too%20late%2C%20if%20they%20ever%20notice%20at%20all.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20the%20more%20nefarious%20side%20of%20the%20equation%2C%20consumers%20lie%20and%20say%20a%20package%20never%20arrived%20or%20was%20stolen%2C%20or%20they%20stick%20a%20different%20product%20back%20in%20the%20box.%20Morin%20says%20Narvar%20had%20a%20client%20during%20the%20pandemic%20who%20started%20to%20see%20a%20trend%20of%20consumers%20returning%20three%20empty%20CD%20cases%20to%20them.%20Someone%20online%20figured%20out%20the%20cases%20weighed%20the%20same%20as%20some%20of%20their%20core%20items%2C%20so%20when%20the%20return%20box%20initially%20got%20weighed%20in%20by%20the%20carrier%2C%20no%20red%20flags%20went%20up%20that%20it%20was%20the%20wrong%20item%20inside.%20Once%20the%20box%20was%20actually%20opened%2C%20the%20refund%20had%20already%20gone%20out.%20Another%20trick%20is%20when%20consumers%20tamper%20with%20return%20labels%20in%20order%20to%20send%20empty%20packages%20to%20the%20wrong%20destination%2C%20so%20they%20can%20just%20claim%20it%20got%20lost%20if%20the%20retailer%20tries%20to%20check.%20They%20keep%20the%20product%2C%20and%20they%20get%20an%20automatic%20refund%20when%20the%20package%20gets%20put%20in%20the%20mail.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHilary%20Koziol%2C%20who%20runs%20the%20Cellar%20Sellers%2C%20an%20online%20consignment%20business%2C%20has%20dealt%20with%20her%20fair%20share%20of%20dishonest%20customers.%20She%20recently%20sold%20a%20sealed%20box%20of%20trading%20cards%20to%20someone%20on%20eBay%20for%20hundreds%20of%20dollars%2C%20and%20the%20buyer%20claimed%20Koziol%20actually%20sent%20a%20box%20with%20a%20pair%20of%20jeans%20inside%2C%20returned%20those%2C%20and%20demanded%20a%20refund%20for%20the%20trading%20cards.%20She%20wound%20up%20opening%20a%20case%20with%20the%20US%20Postal%20Service%20over%20it.%20On%20another%20occasion%2C%20a%20customer%20bought%20a%20%2450%20dress%20from%20her%20on%20Depop%20and%2C%20in%20return%2C%20sent%20back%20an%20old%2C%20makeup-stained%20version%20of%20the%20same%20style.%20%26quot%3BYou%20find%20that%20happens%20a%20lot%20with%20clothing%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20says.%20When%20she%20encounters%20these%20problems%2C%20she%20disputes%20them%20with%20the%20Postal%20Service%20and%20the%20platforms%20she's%20selling%20on%2C%20and%20it's%20%26quot%3Bkind%20of%20a%20crapshoot%26quot%3B%20whether%20she%20wins%20or%20loses%2C%20though%20as%20she%20sells%20more%20stuff%20and%20accumulates%20more%20reviews%2C%20the%20platforms%20tend%20to%20side%20with%20her%20more.%20%26quot%3BEspecially%20if%20it's%20a%20larger-value%20item%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20says%2C%20%26quot%3Bit's%20impacting%20my%20business%20a%20ton.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20lot%20of%20people%20get%20ideas%20online%20and%20on%20social%20media%20for%20different%20return%20tricks%20they%20can%20pull.%20It%20took%20me%20about%20five%20minutes%20of%20searching%20on%20TikTok%20to%20come%20across%20videos%20with%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.tiktok.com%2F%40biggie_boi_q%2Fvideo%2F7204968284519812394%3Flang%3Den%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etips%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.tiktok.com%2F%40amy8fries%2Fvideo%2F7516591047665913118%3Flang%3Den%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eadvice%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20getting%20free%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Famazon-walmart-and-target-let-customers-keep-some-returns-2021-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Erefunds%20from%20Amazon%3C%2Fa%3E.%20There's%20tons%20of%20content%20about%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftarget-cat-and-jack-kids-apparel-millions-of-items-annually-2024-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ETarget's%20Cat%20%26amp%3B%20Jack%20kids%20line's%20generous%20one-year%20return%20policy%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20leads%20many%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmom-return-target-items-kids-shamed-2025-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eparents%20to%20try%20their%20hand%20at%20returning%20well-worn%20clothes%3C%2Fa%3E.%20On%20Reddit%2C%20there's%20a%20forum%20where%20people%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.reddit.com%2Fr%2FCostcoReturns%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecompare%20notes%20on%20Costco%20returns%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20including%20users%20asking%20about%20the%20chances%20the%20company%20might%20accept%20a%20furniture%20return%20five%20years%20after%20it%20was%20purchased%20or%20exchange%20a%20Christmas%20wreath%20after%20the%20leaves%20start%20to%20brown.%20There%20are%20also%20hot%20debates%20about%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.reddit.com%2Fr%2FREI%2Fcomments%2F1ggmlyx%2Freflection_of_my_purchasing_and_returning_habit%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ewhich%20REI%20returns%20may%20count%20as%20abuse%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20almost%20like%20coupon%20sites%20where%20consumers%20have%20been%20trained%20to%20look%20for%20coupons%20and%20discounts%2C%26quot%3B%20Meher%20says.%20%26quot%3BThat's%20starting%20to%20happen%20with%20what%20companies%20offer%20loose%20return%20policies.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EI%20don't%20think%20my%20social%20circle%20is%20the%20most%20crime-prone%20group%20in%20the%20world%2C%20but%20the%20more%20I%20chat%20with%20people%20in%20my%20life%20about%20return%20fraud%20and%20abuse%2C%20especially%20in%20online%20shopping%2C%20the%20more%20I%20realize%20how%20prevalent%20it%20is.%20A%20coworker%20told%20me%20about%20a%20friend%20of%20theirs%20who'd%20returned%20a%20box%20of%20rocks%20to%20a%20retailer%20instead%20of%20a%20television.%20A%20friend%20told%20me%20they'd%20never%20steal%20%E2%80%94%20only%20to%20acknowledge%20they'd%20once%20returned%20a%20big-ticket%20item%20they%20broke%20to%20Amazon%20and%20claimed%20it%20arrived%20broken%2C%20while%20their%20partner%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftarget-return-policy-used-i-am-customer-for-life-2023-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eregularly%20sends%20back%20items%20they've%20worn%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Another%20friend%20said%20that%20whenever%20they%20send%20back%20used%20items%20to%20replace%20new%20ones%20and%20get%20the%20refund%2C%20they%20make%20sure%20the%20seller%20is%20a%20big%20corporation%2C%20not%20a%20small%20mom-and-pop%20shop.%20I%20tried%20to%20do%20the%20bracketing%20thing%20with%20two%20sets%20of%20curtains%20last%20summer%20but%20failed.%20I%20was%20too%20lazy%20to%20return%20the%20set%20I%20didn't%20want%20within%20the%20return%20window%2C%20so%20it's%20accumulating%20dust%20under%20my%20bed.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETo%20many%20people%2C%20low-level%20return%20fraud%20feels%20like%20a%20victimless%20crime%20%E2%80%94%20they're%20not%20exactly%20losing%20sleep%20over%20a%20giant%20corporation%20losing%20a%20few%20dollars%20here%20and%20there.%20People%20assume%20retailers%20don't%20really%20care%20that%20much%2C%20since%20they'll%20often%20send%20a%20refund%20before%20getting%20the%20item%20back%2C%20if%20they%20bother%20to%20recollect%20an%20item%20at%20all.%20Companies%20have%20also%20given%20people%20such%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fstore-best-return-policy-2017-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Elong%20leash%20on%20accepting%20returns%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20consumers%20may%20not%20blink%20at%20hauling%20grass%20shears%20smeared%20with%20clippings%20back%20to%20the%20Target%20counter%20after%20six%20months%20of%20use.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMegan%20Wyatt%2C%20the%20owner%20of%20Wit%20%26amp%3B%20Whimsy%20Toys%2C%20a%20brick-and-mortar%20retailer%20in%20California%2C%20says%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Fstyle%2Fstores-with-longest-return-policies%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Elax%20return%20policies%3C%2Fa%3E%20the%20big%20guys%20offer%20customers%20have%20been%20a%20headache%20for%20her.%20%26quot%3BThey'll%20just%20take%20pretty%20much%20any%20return%2C%20it%20feels%20like%2C%20these%20days.%20And%20so%20customers%20feel%20like%20they%20can%20do%20that%20at%20small%20businesses%20as%20well%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20says.%20Her%20store%20has%20to%20essentially%20%26quot%3Btrain%20customers%20that%20you%20can't%20expect%20to%20return%20things%20at%20a%20small%20business%20the%20way%20that%20you%20would%20at%20Target%2C%20Walmart%2C%20Amazon%2C%20places%20like%20that.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERetailers%20big%20and%20small%20aren't%20having%20a%20good%20time%20with%20return%20fraud%20and%20are%20cracking%20down.%20Many%20are%20axing%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ffree-shipping-free-returns-online-shopping-companies-charging-expensive-amazon-2024-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efree%20returns%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20tightening%20return%20windows%2C%20or%20otherwise%20implementing%20stricter%20returns%20policies.%20Companies%20such%20as%20REI%20and%20ASOS%20have%20started%20to%20ban%20certain%20customers%20over%20return%20abuse.%20Some%20retailers%20are%20using%20aggregated%20data%20to%20try%20to%20identify%20bad%20actors%2C%20whether%20they're%20a%20previous%20customer%20or%20not.%20If%20a%20consumer%20is%20continually%20taking%20advantage%20of%20return%20policies%20at%20X%20retailer%2C%20Y%20retailer%20may%20know%20even%20before%20they%20click%20to%20buy.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMeher%2C%20from%20Loop%2C%20says%20personalized%20return%20policies%20are%20starting%20to%20become%20more%20common%2C%20too.%20%26quot%3BSo%2C%20being%20able%20to%20incentivize%20good%20customers%20and%20giving%20them%20good%20return%20policies%20and%20disincentivize%20bad%20consumers%20and%20people%20who%20return%20a%20lot%20and%20giving%20them%20different%20return%20windows%20or%20different%20return%20policies%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20says.%20%26quot%3BThat%20is%20also%20starting%20to%20become%20more%20important%20as%20retailers%20look%20into%2C%20'How%20do%20I%20make%20sure%20that%20I%20don't%20piss%20off%20my%20good%20customers%3F'%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAcross%20the%20consumer%20economy%2C%20there's%20a%20pervasive%20us-versus-them%20sentiment%20between%20companies%20and%20their%20customers.%20Many%20consumers%20feel%20like%20businesses%20%E2%80%94%20especially%20the%20big%20ones%20%E2%80%94%20are%20swindling%20them%20and%20squeezing%20them%20for%20every%20penny%2C%20so%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmiddle-class-shoplifting-retail-theft-crime-stealing-stores-2024-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ewhen%20they%20have%20a%20chance%20to%20strike%20back%2C%20why%20not%3C%2Fa%3E%3F%20Maybe%20that%20means%20putting%20a%20brick%20in%20a%20return%20box%20and%20hoping%20nobody%20notices%20it's%20not%20an%20iPad.%20Or%20maybe%20it's%20just%20seeing%20that%20package%20you'd%20already%20declared%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Ftech%2Fwhat-to-do-if-your-package-gets-stolen%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Estolen%3C%2Fa%3E%20arrived%20three%20days%20late%20and%20not%20trying%20too%20hard%20to%20give%20back%20that%20refund%20that%20already%20came%20through.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2